editorialSummary.text: Stylish nightspot featuring live DJ events & a lounge for cocktails & bar bites.

originalText.text: I actually came the other night for a show. They changed the dress code policy at the last minute when people were already on their way to the show so there were so many people they would not let in because of it regardless if you spent your hard earned money on those tickets. The security kept taunting the girls snickering and talking about them like they themselves were little girls and said “no refunds”. That is completely unprofessional they should learn to be grown men and control themselves. The show started at midnight so of course there were no stores open for them to change. So they have girls who came by themselves standing all alone outside trying to figure out how to get home I felt so bad for them! I lived not too far so me and my friends managed to get changed and go back to the venue but was yet again disappointed. Was not informed about the additional charges and I was also robbed of a couple of my belongings. Even the staff were not professional. There was this blonde girl who kept insisting to me and my friends that we ordered more drinks and she kept badgering us the whole night. All in all it was just a bad experience and I wouldn’t go back to be honest because I haven’t been to a nightclub that had so many issues all in one.

originalText.text: We were only there to support DJs that were playing there that night. We also knew this place used to be the Playboy Club and wanted to see what the hype was about. I understand security was doing their job but it was really excessive search, you might as well just take my entire purse and the body check got a bit way too handsy. I wasn't entirely impressed with the inside (a typical club) and the bathrooms were dirty and in bad condition, I'm not sure if it was just me, but every stall I went in had bloody tampons/tissue just left laying around (pretty disgusting). Overall, I don't care for it and won't be back.

originalText.text: I was a little skeptical about this place because of the reviews but I went the other night and honestly had an amazing time. The music was great, the vibe was amazing! My friends and I loved it we will definitely be going back. The prices are a little over the top but it is an upscale club so I get it. I’ll be going back for sure !!

originalText.text: My experience: I don’t know what is happening in that place because I have never actually been in side. I am staying next door unfortunately. Here I am in my hotel minding my own business when I hear this completely obtrusive argument in sue over a slur that was supposedly said inside of the club. Based on witness statements the security guards dragged two women out … hands around the chest. All I heard was yelling and screaming. Sounded like two cats breading while they also clawed their eyes out. This went on for over an hour. The ear plugs helped but wow. Idk what is going on in there but I don’t know how anyone doesn’t need a cochlear implant after all of this noise. Don’t go near it. If you do bring ear plugs.

originalText.text: Where do I start? The promoter who made promises and didn’t deliver? To us ending up having to pay almost $500 extra to listen to trash music all night (techno- zero hip hop and Afro beats, ALL NIGHT) to them saying Kodak Black is coming and him not touching the stage until after 330a (club closes at 4) to the rude staff at the door who was refusing to let us in until we contacted our promoter and he said it was ok (embarrassing) to us almost getting charged extra for late guests when we had a section. To the “section” getting moved because they booked an artist and we were placed in the “lounge” which is completely separate from the party? To our “section” being crammed close to another party? NEVER AGAIN. ZERO STARS.
